&lt;p&gt;You&#39;ll own the Azure platform strategy across the organization, including:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leading production workload migrations into a new Azure subscription and resource group structure with minimal business disruption.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Designing scalable Azure architectures alongside engineering teams before applications are built.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establishing Infrastructure as Code standards using Terraform or Bicep.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Building and maintaining CI/CD pipelines using Azure DevOps or GitHub Actions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Defining governance across multiple Azure subscriptions, management groups, RBAC, policies, and naming standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Driving platform observability through Azure Monitor, Application Insights, Log Analytics, dashboards, and alerting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leading platform incident response, root cause analysis, and operational improvements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Designing secure identity and access strategies using Microsoft Entra ID.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implementing modern networking and security patterns including Azure Front Door, Private Endpoints, and NSGs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Optimizing cloud costs while maintaining scalability and performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mentoring engineers and acting as the technical authority for cloud infrastructure and DevOps practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Helping shape operational standards for emerging Azure AI workloads.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
